The paper proposes a novel Winner-Take-All (WTA) architecture employing neurons with nonlinear dendrites and an online unsupervised structural plasticity rule for training it. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the proposed learning rule is inspired by spike time dependent plasticity (STDP), which is a common technique used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses classification of random Poisson spike time inputs, which is a common problem in systems and control (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, and cs.CV, in that order.
